{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "booking-api-collection",
		"name": "Booking Module API",
		"description": "Complete API test collection for the University Operations Booking Module. This collection includes all endpoints for booking management, resource scheduling, and administrative operations.\n\n**Base URL**: http://localhost:8080\n\n**Authentication**: JWT Bearer Token (Required for all endpoints)\n\n**Setup Instructions**:\n1. Import this collection into Postman\n2. Set up environment variables:\n   - `baseUrl`: http://localhost:8080\n   - `jwtToken`: Your JWT authentication token\n3. Use the \"Login\" request to get JWT token\n4. Set the `jwtToken` environment variable from login response\n\n**User Roles**:\n- ADMIN: Full access to all endpoints\n- LECTURER/STUDENT: Limited access to own bookings and public resources\n- BOOKING_MANAGER: Administrative booking management",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
		"_exporter_id": "booking-module-export"
	},
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Authentication",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Login (Get JWT Token)",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"// Extract JWT token from response and set environment variable",
									"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
									"    const response = pm.response.json();",
									"    if (response.token) {",
									"        pm.environment.set('jwtToken', response.token);",
									"        pm.collectionVariables.set('jwtToken', response.token);",
									"        console.log('JWT token set successfully');",
									"    }",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"email\": \"admin@uniops.edu\",\n    \"password\": \"admin123\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login",
							"host": [
								"{{baseUrl}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"auth",
								"login"
							]
						}
					},
					"response": []
				}
			],
			"description": "Authentication endpoints for getting JWT tokens"
		},
